returns._0: A string representing the complete JSON object.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params.versionIndex: The index in the version history array.

returns._0: The string value at the specified version index.

params.key: The JSON key whose version history is requested.

returns._0: A JSON array string with all historical values for the key.

params.replace: If true, replaces the latest value of an existing key. If false, reverts if the key exists.

json().notice: Returns the JSON object in its latest state.

valueAt(string,uint256).notice: Returns a value for a key at a specific version index.

version(string).notice: Returns the version history of a specific key.

write(string[],string[],bool).notice: Writes new values to the JSON object.
